      <!-- Detail -->
      <div class="container" id="detail">
        <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-lg-3 align-items-stretch g-4 py-5">
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
              <!-- <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/150" class="card-img-top" alt="..."> -->
              <div class="card-body" style="border: solid 3px rgb(255, 96, 3);">
                <h5 class="card-title" style="background-color: rgb(236, 233, 8);">
                     . Here are some guidelines for a Bachelor of Technology (BTech)
                  degree:
                </h5>
                <p class="card-text" id="text1">
                  <b>Eligibility:-</b><br />
                  To be eligible for admission to a BTech program, you must have
                  studied Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics in Class 12 from a
                  recognized board. You must also have obtained a minimum of
                  55–75% aggregate marks in these subjects, though this may vary
                  by institution.....
                </p>
                <p class="card-text d-none" id="more-text1">
                  <b>Duration:-</b> <br />
                  A BTech degree is an undergraduate engineering degree that
                  typically takes four years to complete. However, the minimum
                  period is four academic years and the maximum is eight
                  academic years.
                  <b> Curriculum:-</b> <br />
                  A BTech curriculum is designed to provide a well-rounded
                  engineering education. The course is typically divided into
                  eight semesters, with each semester covering a core and
                  elective subjects.
                  <b> Lateral entry:-</b><br />
                  Candidates who have completed a Diploma course in a relevant
                  engineering field can enter the BTech program in its second
                </p>
                <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-success" id="read-more1"
                  >Read More</a
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Column 2 -->
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
              <!-- <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/150" class="card-img-top" alt="..."> -->
              <div class="card-body" style="border: solid 3px rgb(255, 96, 3);">
                <h5 class="card-title" style="background-color: rgb(236, 233, 8);">
                  .Here are some guidelines for Bachelor of Computer Applications
                  (BCA)admission:
                </h5>
                <p class="card-text" id="text2">
                  <b>Eligibility:-</b> <br />
                  Candidates must be Indian citizens and have passed the 10+2 or
                  equivalent examination with at least 40–50% marks. Mathematics
                  is a compulsory subject. Candidates from reserved computer
                  basec work is compalsary categories may be eligible for a 5%
                  relaxation..
                </p>
                <p class="card-text d-none" id="more-text2">
                  <b>Programs:-</b> <br />
                  There are several types of BCA programs, including regular,
                  integrated, flexible, and specialized programs. Some programs
                  may also include industry-integrated certification or an
                  internship . <br /><b>Skills:-</b> <br />
                  The BCA course teaches students various IT skills, including
                  programming languages, database management systems, cyber
                  security, operating systems, computer networks, and web
                  development <br />
                  <b>Admission process:-</b><br />
                  Admission is usually based on merit and entrance exams. Some
                  universities may also conduct an interview.
                </p>
                <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-success" id="read-more2"
                  >Read More</a
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Column 3 -->
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
              <!-- <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/150" class="card-img-top" alt="..."> -->
              <div class="card-body" style="border: solid 3px rgb(255, 96, 3);">
                <h5 class="card-title" style="background-color: rgb(236, 233, 8);">
                  .Master of Computer Applications (MCA) has several
                  guidelines, including
                </h5>
                <p class="card-text" id="text3">
                  <b>Annual e-filing:-</b><br />
                  Companies must e-file documents with the Registrar of
                  Companies (RoC). These include: Balance sheet: Form 23AC
                  Profit and loss account: Form 23ACA Annual return:, or Form
                  21A for companies without share capital Compliance
                  certificate: Form 66 for companies with paid up capital
                  between Rs. 10 lakh.
                </p>
                <p class="card-text d-none" id="more-text3">
                  <b>Company names:-</b><br />
                  Company names must not: <br />
                  Resemble the names of existing companies. <br />
                  Violate any existing laws. <br />
                  Be considered undesirable by the Central Government. <br />
                  <b>Responsible business conduct:-</b> <br />
                  Businesses should be aware of their social, environmental, and
                  economic responsibilities. They should also: Minimize negative
                  impacts on society Promote the well-being of all segments of
                  society Be sensitive to the concerns of local communities
                  Minimize the negative impacts of displacement of people
                </p>
                <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-success" id="read-more3"
                  >Read More</a
                >
              </div>
            </div>
